params._limit: The max limit of HouseNFT . Ex = 1000
The max limit of HouseNFT which whitelisted users can mint altogether. Ex - 500

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.

params._id: Id of token state of whitelist minting can be set separately. This function should only be called by the whitelisted users.Admint can turn off public minting when they wanna start whitelist minting

mint(uint256).notice: This function will ve used to mint an NFT, user need to pass the token ID which they wanna mint

setPublicHouseMintingLimit(uint256).notice: Owner will set public minting before enabling public mint, as public minting is Enabled by default, Admint should set this number just after deploying the contract.

setPublicMintingMode().notice: This function is for turning the mode of public minting On or Off. This function is admin controlled & if the status is Enabled then the above mint() will work, if the status is Disabled then the mint() will not work.

setWhitelistHouseMintingLimit(uint256).notice: Admin must set this number just before enabling the Whitelist minting mode, by default this mode is Disabled.

setWhitelistMintingMode().notice: This function is for turning the mode of whitelisting minting On or Off. This function is admin controlled & if the status is Enabled then the above whitelistMint() will work, if the status is Disabled then the whitelistMint() will not work.

statements.documentation:
As a user mint a nft of same id only 1 time we are checking that the balance for that token id is 0 or not. IF not 0 i.e if the user has the NFT with same ID
 this will revert
If claim phase deactivated then one user can mint only one house NFT, after first minting the status will be changed to True.
